<ServiceLayout {...pageData}>
  
  <section class="section bg-white">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Understanding Legal Translation in the UAE</h2>
      <div class="content-prose">
        <p>Legal translation operates within a specific regulatory framework. The Ministry of Justice licenses translators for court proceedings and government submissions.</p>
        
        <div class="key-point">
          <h4><i class="fas fa-stamp"></i> MOJ Certification Required</h4>
          <p>Dubai Courts, Abu Dhabi Judicial Department, and all UAE authorities require:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Official MOJ stamp on translation</li>
            <li>Translator's registration number</li>
            <li>QR code for verification</li>
          </ul>
          <p>Without this certification, your document will be rejected.</p>
        </div>
        
        <h3>Legal vs General Translation</h3>
        <p>Legal translation differs in important ways:</p>
        <ul class="diff-list">
          <li><strong>Precise terminology:</strong> Terms have exact meanings that vary by jurisdiction</li>
          <li><strong>Dual legal systems:</strong> UAE mainland uses civil law; DIFC/ADGM use common law</li>
          <li><strong>Binding consequences:</strong> Errors can change legal effect</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h3>Court Document Requirements</h3>
        <p>UAE courts maintain specific requirements:</p>
        <ul class="req-list">
          <li>Translation must be complete—no partial translations</li>
          <li>Translator must certify accuracy</li>
          <li>Multi-page documents need stamping on each page</li>
        </ul>
        
        <div class="deadline-warning">
          <h4><i class="fas fa-clock"></i> Court Deadlines Matter</h4>
          <p>Filing deadlines are strictly enforced. Missing a deadline because translation wasn't ready can seriously harm your case. We structure our service to accommodate urgent court requirements.</p>
        </div>
        
        <h3>Contract Translation Considerations</h3>
        <p>Contracts present particular challenges:</p>
        <ul class="challenge-list">
          <li>Conditional language and defined terms</li>
          <li>References to other documents or legal provisions</li>
          <li>Maintaining consistency throughout the document</li>
        </ul>
        
        <div class="bilingual-note">
          <p><strong>Bilingual contracts:</strong> Many UAE businesses use Arabic and English versions. Courts typically give precedence to Arabic for mainland proceedings. Arabic translation quality is critical.</p>
        </div>
        
        <h3>Supporting Law Firms</h3>
        <p>We work with law firms across the UAE. We accommodate:</p>
        <ul class="support-list">
          <li>Confidentiality protocols</li>
          <li>Billing preferences</li>
          <li>Volume arrangements</li>
          <li>Dedicated contacts for ongoing matters</li>
        </ul>
        <p>For complex litigation with large document volumes, we arrange dedicated translator teams.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

